The paper deals with the problem of knowledge extraction and relation discovery from complex heterogeneous networks, which is a common problem in the field of social informatics (cs.SI). The proposed algorithms are designed to be scalable and accurate, which suggests that they may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of the Apache Giraph platform for designing and running distributed graph algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of databases (cs.DB) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the case study on drug repositioning suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
